description:
This omnibus edition contains volumes 4-6 of the hit manga series Dance in the Vampire Bund.

Mina Tepes, the princess of vampires, has set up a special district for vampires off the coast of Tokyo. Mina’s extensive preparations include founding a school that she herself attends, along with her passionately loyal werewolf bodyguard, Akira, in tow.

Ever since the day the school opened, rival vampire factions have opposed Mina’s grand vision. They continue targeting the human populace in order to smear Mina’s reputation and sabotage her well-laid plans of vampires and humans living together in peace.
name: Vol. 4-6

volume.name: Dance In the Vampire Bund Omnibus

description: Long considered as one of Osamu Tezuka's most political narratives, Ayako is also considered to be one of his most challenging. Initially set in the aftermath of World War II, Ayako focuses its attention on the Tenge clan, a once powerful family of landowners living in a rural community in northern Japan. The war and American occupation have begun to erode the fabric that binds them all together. The increasing influence of political, economic and social change begins to tear into the many Tenge siblings, and they decide to turn their collective rage on what they believe to be the source of their troubles - the newest member of the Tenge family, the youngest sister Ayako.
name: GN

description:
HORRIFYING HALLOWEEN

Sunako and the handsome foursome cannot be stopped! Sunako dresses up as a pirate to get her aunt's jewelry back! For Halloween, Sunako and the Princess host a horror party! And then, the Princess' fiance Ranmaru gets close with Sunako in bed… How will Kyouhei react?
name: Vol. 30

description:
Join novelist and part-time detective Lizzie Newton and her dashing suitor, the former lawyer-turned-butler, Edwin White, as they lead Inspector Grey further down the rabbit hole of mystery and intrigue!

In this beautifully illustrated shoujo series, Lizzie continues to solve murders with panache and wit in a setting that’s part Agatha Christie and part Jane Austen.
name: Vol. 2

description:
Alter Ego takes a red and green look at those sensational stereoscopic comics of the 1950s in a special 3-D issue! There's an in-depth feature assembled and annotated by Ray (3-D) Zone, featuring never-before-revealed secrets of the era! Then prepare yourself, as we reproduce actual 1950s 3-D art by Simon & Kirby, Kubert, Meskin, Powell, Maurer, Nostrand, Swan, Boring, Schwartz, Mooney, Shores, Tuska, and many others! This issue comes polybagged, and includes free 3-D glasses so you can view the art in all its dimensions!

Continued in Alter Ego #126.

You wanted the best, and you got the best, the hottest comic book in the land - Creepy Kofy Movie Time Comic! Bringing back the horror in horror for sure! Featuring tales ranging from werewolves to cave girls, all drawn by some of the best talents in comics like Ken Hooper and Trevor Von Eeden!

Reckless guardian angel Zachary has an unusual assignment. He's meant to save the soul of Miranda, high-school theater wannabe turned glamorous royal vampire. Completely devoted to Miranda, Zachary takes his demotion to human form in stride, taking a job as the princess's personal assistant. Of course, this means he has to balance his soul-saving efforts with planning the Master's fast-approaching Death Day gala.
name: GN

description: This multiple award-winning comic magazine features the hilarious misadventures of a group of gamers (the Knights) and their friends, along with useful role-playing and other articles for gamers, from a gamer's perspective. It's a slice of (fantasy) life in strips, articles, reviews and features, and a wonderful celebration of the gaming culture!

After Mymble's family comes to visit the Moomins, her littlest and most badly behaved sister, Little My, is left behind. She promises to behave if she is given Moomin's bedroom; Moomin, tired of being forced out of his room, decides to build a house where all the rooms will belong to him. With Little My helping out, things are sure to go awry, but in the end, Moomin's house-building misadventures teach him the value of a home.
name: GN

description: Moominvalley is flooded, so Snorkmaiden and Moomin head out to rescue anyone stranded in the deluge. They bring home Miss La Goona, the leading lady of the visiting circus, who turns out to be quite a demanding houseguest. Nonetheless, Moomin, having read a few too many romantic novels, falls head over heels in love with her, and chaos ensues.
name: GN

description: Vesper quickly gets up to speed on her new super-powered guardian, Corrick's abilities, but learns little else about him before. Could her Father's return be the beginning of the events that lead to the carnage seen at the beginning of the series?

Just as True's team of super powered conmen scramble to keep their plan alive, they discover a new Vegas crime lord by the name of Crosswords might be behind all of their problems. Is this the end or only the beginning?

The Acts of Vengeance are here, and no hero is left untouched! Witness some of the most unexpected battles of all time! Wolverine vs. Tiger Shark! Dr. Strange vs. Hobgoblin! The Punisher vs. Dr. Doom! Daredevil vs. Ultron! Power Pack vs. Typhoid Mary! And while the Fantastic Four fight against the passing of a Super Hero Registration Act, Psylocke is changed forever at the hands of Mojo! Collecting Collecting Fantastic Four (1961) #334-336; Wolverine (1988) #19-20; Dr. Strange, Sorceror Supreme (1988) #11-13; Incredible Hulk (1968) #363; Punisher (1987) #28-29; Punisher War Journal (1988) #12-13; Marc Spector: Moon Knight (1989) #8-10; Daredevil (1964) #275-276; Power Pack (1984) #53; Alpha Flight (1983) #79-80; New Mutants (1983) #84-86; Uncanny X-Men #256-258; X-Factor (1986) #49-50; Damage Control (1989) #1-4; and Web Of Spider-Man #64-65.
name: HC

description:
The hit web comic now coming to print! Vesper Gray is wrested from her stiff Victorian setting when a mysterious spirit saves her life. What secrets does her new friend hold, and how does it tie into her father's mysterious expeditions to strange places? And why do poeple want them dead!

For its first offering, Brewhouse Comics is proud to present: BIGFOOT – SWORD OF THE EARTHMAN, an epic six-issue mini-series involving the world-famous sasquatch and his quest to defeat the ruthless emperor of a barbarian planet. Equal parts Conan and Flash Gordon, the otherworldly saga is written by Josh S. Henaman with art by Andy Taylor. BIGFOOT – SWORD OF THE EARTHMAN is not the story of how Bigfoot became a myth on Earth. It’s the story of how he became a legend of the stars.

Quoted Praises For Issue One

The following are quotes that Brewhouse has published inside their comic books

"The Sheer fun of the idea is awesome... And it made me want to get back into comics." -Gene D.

"B:SOTE is kind of mainlining the Planet Hulk Series while mashing your face into some classic issue of Hellboy" - Annalee Newitz - io9

"This is a smart, wild fusion mash-up..." - Geek Life

“Feels like Jack Kirby and Edgar Rice Burroughs had a love child, and that love child was awesome!” - Fanboy Comics

“Bigfoot is one of those rare titles that make me remember how much fun comics can be.” - Bag & Bored

"A sword-slingin' Sasquatch fighting monsters and aliens on Mars?! SIgn me up" - Sean Whitley - Director, Souther Fried Bigfoot

"A buyer would be proud to have this in his bookshelves at home!" - Broken Frontier
name: Devil in the Desert

description:
Bigfoot is Back! Issue #2 of the sword, sorcery and sasquatch epic continues the interplanetary barbarian adventure of Bigfoot and his alien sidekick And it couldn’t be more out of this world!

Continuing the epic tale, BIGFOOT – SWORD OF THE EARTHMAN #2 finds Bigfoot and his sidekick, Bagworm, as reluctant soldiers of a desolate desert outpost. Their duty? Protect the innocent from a locust-like race of moth-vampires. Of course, wherever a 7-ft tall ape-man is concerned, things don’t go quite as planned.

Brewhouse Comics is proud to present the next chapter of BIGFOOT – SWORD OF THE EARTHMAN, the monumental six-issue mini-series involving the world-famous sasquatch and his quest to defeat the ruthless emperor of a barbarian planet. Written by Josh S. Henaman with art by Kubert alums Andy Taylor (line art) and Thomas Bonvillain (colorist), BIGFOOT – SWORD OF THE EARTHMAN is not the story of how Bigfoot became a myth on Earth. It’s the story of how he became a legend of the stars.

Quoted Praises For Issue Two

The following are quotes that Brewhouse has published inside their comic books

"Just finished the second comic in a moving car and now I am carsick but it was totally worth it." -Caleb M.

"The entire premise of the comic is as awesome as the title." - Tommy Lutz - ReadComicBooks.net

"The whole package is something I think most comic fans would have trouble putting down" - Cory Thrall - Bag & Bored

“Bigfoot: SOTE is a big weird comic book that deifes description... But, holy cow is it fun/// Noboby is doing anything like this.” -Ben Rhodes - Fanboy Comics

“Bigfoot: SOTE stands up neatly on its own fairy feet in a comic form as an entertaining read." - Obsidian Mercutio Tesla - Schlock! Webzine

"Bigfoot is sword- weilding warrior on Mars and is referred to as the Earthman? And he fights scary alien creaturs and beats up on Martians? You had me at Bigfoot." - Guy Edwards - BigfootLunchClub.com

"Brandon Burpee likes it, if anyone else doesn't $#@% his &!@$." - Brandon Burpee - 4 Color News and Brews
name: Soldiers At the Heart of the Sun

description:
The mind is its own place, and in itself Can make a heaven of hell, a hell of heaven.’ John Milton!

Cassandra Anderson, Psi Division’s finest Judge, has faced many tough challenges in her career. From saving Mega-City One’s total annihilation at the hands of the Dark Judges to dealing with a loss of faith in the Justice System, Anderson may have thought that she had already faced her hardest challenges. But something evil from the depths of space is about to crash down into the ‘Big Meg’, presenting the Judges with a bigger crisis than they have ever faced before!

These further adventures of everybody’s favourite Psi Judge are written by Alan Grant (Batman, Lobo) and features the stunning artwork of Arthur Ranson (Mazeworld) and Trevor Hairsine (Cla$$war).

THIS VOLUME INCLUDES THE STORIES

description: Still reeling from the destruction of Metropolis, news from a war-torn country creates a tipping point for the Man of Steel. He decides it's time for him to take a more proactive role in stopping man's inhumanity to man. But does the sudden appearance of Wonder Woman mean he's created a new enemy or converted an ally to his cause?
name: Chapter 6
